{"build_type":"library","module_name":"render-buffer-window-bytes-hexadecimal","package_name":"render-buffer-window-bytes-hexadecimal","description":"Tail-recursive: write the lowercase hexadecimal encoding of buf[i, m) into out, two ASCII characters per source byte (high nibble then low), so read-file can return arbitrary binary windows (NUL bytes, invalid UTF-8) as a valid JSON string. out must hold at least two times the window length plus one. Params: buf, i, m, out.","function_definitions":{"render-buffer-window-bytes-hexadecimal":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"buf","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"i","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"m","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"out","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"two","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":2},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"four","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":4},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"ten","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":10},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"fifteen","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":15},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"ff","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":255},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"d48","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":48},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"d87","variable_